track_notes:
I believe most people activating Bredon do so by driving up to Kemerton barn, thus gaining quite a bit of height then walking up top the top. This is a fine walk, but Bredon is an expansive hill, and there are a some good alternatives.  These routes are an attempt to mark them out and thus make the best of my local hill.
  
Woollas Hall Farm is below Bredons escarpment, so from this angle it looks more of a hill, but the path is never too steep.  2.28km, 270M and took me 36 minutes.
track_title: Bredon Hill from Woollas Hall Farm

track_notes: There is room for about five cars at the road end. The track from the tower through SO 9582 3990 is a permissive track. More info on Catterblog under July 2013.
track_title: G/CE-003 Bredon Hill from the Bells Castle parking place

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 1hr 55m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. track_title: Bredon Hill Linear from Kemerton. May 2020.
